The article is a transcript of a joint press conference between President Obama and President Karzai. They discuss the progress made in Afghanistan, including the transition of security to Afghan forces and the decrease in violence. They also discuss future plans for the US military presence in Afghanistan, including training and assisting Afghan forces, and targeting counterterrorism missions. Both presidents emphasize the importance of reconciliation and peace in Afghanistan, as well as the need for political and economic progress. They also address concerns about corruption and the rights of Afghan women.